    ex:postID "LIPITOR.117" ;
    ex:sentenceText "still have pain in feet and legs, since doctor made me continue this lipitor crippling medicine from hell and when i refused to take it the 2nd time, even though they continued to tell me that i could die if i did not take it, with my response being that i could live with agonizing pain and be disabled on this medication or possibly not die from this medication and still provide for my family by working. still have pain in feet and legs, since doctor made me continue this lipitor crippling medicine from hell and when i refused to take it the 2nd time, even though they continued to tell me that i could die if i did not take it, with my response being that i could live with agonizing pain and be disabled on this medication or possibly not die from this medication and still provide for my family by working. still have pain in feet and legs, since doctor made me continue this lipitor crippling medicine from hell and when i refused to take it the 2nd time, even though they continued to tell me that i could die if i did not take it, with my response being that i could live with agonizing pain and be disabled on this medication or possibly not die from this medication and still provide for my family by working. that was long ago and my feet still hurt so bad by the end of my work day, because they decided i should take simcor in its place. now i had no ideas at the time about statin drugs until i found this website, i had been on simcor for 1 month and stopped it immediately when i realized that it was perpetuating my foot ankle pain."^^xsd:string .

