    ex:postID "LIPITOR.323" ;
    ex:sentenceText "i take zoloft for major depression and it works well. however, within days of starting lipitor, i started feeling the adverse side effects depression, anxiety, spaced-out feeling, lack of concentration, insomnia which are pretty much how i felt when i was experiencing major depression. however, within days of starting lipitor, i started feeling the adverse side effects depression, anxiety, spaced-out feeling, lack of concentration, insomnia which are pretty much how i felt when i was experiencing major depression. however, within days of starting lipitor, i started feeling the adverse side effects depression, anxiety, spaced-out feeling, lack of concentration, insomnia which are pretty much how i felt when i was experiencing major depression. however, within days of starting lipitor, i started feeling the adverse side effects depression, anxiety, spaced-out feeling, lack of concentration, insomnia which are pretty much how i felt when i was experiencing major depression. however, within days of starting lipitor, i started feeling the adverse side effects depression, anxiety, spaced-out feeling, lack of concentration, insomnia which are pretty much how i felt when i was experiencing major depression. the thing is, if i were to stop taking zoloft today, it would be months before i felt the depression returning, and it would take months to get back to normal when i restarted zoloft. just to be sure, i started taking lipitor a second time, and the depression came back within one or two days."^^xsd:string .

